        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The joy of wearing the perfect engagement ring is unmatched, but choosing one can be a daunting task! The perfect engagement ring, adorned with diamonds and set in precious metals like gold and platinum, requires exceptional craftsmanship and top-notch quality. From selecting the right diamond to deciding on the ideal metal and style, every choice reflects your love story and should be just as special! In this guide, we cover everything you need to know to select the perfect engagement ring! </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kKqW7n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Choosing The Right Metal ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Choosing The Right Metal </h2>",
            "custom_id": "radiant",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_yYFrht": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Choosing The Right Metal  Paragraph ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Before browsing for rings, it is important to select the metal. The metal of the ring decides the entire tone and durability of the ring. Both gold and platinum are durable and last a lifetime. Each one - platinum, white gold, yellow gold, and rose gold- has something unique to offer. </p><p>Platinum is for the ones who choose elegance, who wish to move with grace and poise. Platinum is hypoallergenic and long-lasting. With the natural white color that doesn’t come with a rhodium plating, a platinum ring’s diamond radiates an unparalleled shine. </p><p>White gold looks luxurious. It is an elegant and modern choice that has a versatile look for both western and ethnic wear. Unlike platinum, which is naturally white in color, white gold has a rhodium plating that gives it the whiteness. The shine of this can sustain for a lifetime if you know how to care for your engagement ring. </p><p>Yellow Gold is the most preferred classic metal choice for diamond rings. It adds a vintage appeal and is a timeless choice. </p><p>Rose gold is becoming increasingly popular as a custom diamond ring, as it elicits a feeling of romance. The soft tone of rose gold, with its blush hue, looks charming </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Round Cut Solitaire Engagement Ring",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Round Cut Solitaire Engagement Ring</h2>",
            "custom_id": "round-cut",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
